#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an11.6"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an11.6:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 11 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 11 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an11.6:0.2"
msgid "1. Nissayavagga "
msgstr "1. Dependence "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an11.6:0.3"
msgid "6. Byasanasutta "
msgstr "6. Disasters "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. VAR: etthantare pāṭho sī, syā1-3, kaṃ, pā1 potthakesu na
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an11.6:1.1"
msgid "“Yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu akkosako paribhāsako ariyūpavādo sabrahmacārīnaṃ, ṭhānametaṃ avakāso yaṃ so ekādasannaṃ byasanānaṃ aññataraṃ byasanaṃ nigaccheyya. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, any mendicant who abuses and insults their spiritual companions, speaking ill of the noble ones, will, without a doubt, fall into one or other of these eleven disasters. "

#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.318, sc2
msgctxt "an11.6:2.1"
msgid "Katamesaṃ ekādasannaṃ? "
msgstr "What eleven? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an11.6:2.2"
msgid "Anadhigataṃ nādhigacchati, "
msgstr "They don’t achieve the unachieved. "

msgctxt "an11.6:2.3"
msgid "adhigatā parihāyati, "
msgstr "What they have achieved falls away. "

msgctxt "an11.6:2.4"
msgid "saddhammassa na vodāyanti, "
msgstr "They don’t refine their good qualities. "

msgctxt "an11.6:2.5"
msgid "saddhammesu vā adhimāniko hoti, "
msgstr "They overestimate their good qualities. "

msgctxt "an11.6:2.6"
msgid "anabhirato vā brahmacariyaṃ carati, "
msgstr "Or they live the spiritual life dissatisfied. "

msgctxt "an11.6:2.7"
msgid "aññataraṃ vā saṃkiliṭṭhaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati, "
msgstr "Or they commit a corrupt offense. "

msgctxt "an11.6:2.8"
msgid "sikkhaṃ vā paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattati, "
msgstr "Or they reject the training and return to a lesser life. "

msgctxt "an11.6:2.9"
msgid "gāḷhaṃ vā rogātaṅkaṃ phusati, "
msgstr "Or they contract a severe illness. "

msgctxt "an11.6:2.10"
msgid "ummādaṃ vā pāpuṇāti cittakkhepaṃ vā, "
msgstr "Or they go mad and lose their mind. "

msgctxt "an11.6:2.11"
msgid "sammūḷho kālaṃ karoti, "
msgstr "They feel lost when they die. "

msgctxt "an11.6:2.12"
msgid "kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati—"
msgstr "And when their body breaks up, after death, they are reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an11.6:2.13"
msgid "yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu akkosako paribhāsako ariyūpavādo sabrahmacārīnaṃ, ṭhānametaṃ avakāso yaṃ so imesaṃ ekādasannaṃ byasanānaṃ aññataraṃ byasanaṃ nigaccheyya. "
msgstr "Any mendicant who abuses and insults their spiritual companions, speaking ill of the noble ones, will, without a doubt, fall into one or other of these eleven disasters. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
#. VAR: akkosako paribhāsako → akkosakaparibhāsako (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an11.6:3.1"
msgid "Yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu akkosako paribhāsako ariyūpavādo sabrahmacārīnaṃ, aṭṭhānametaṃ anavakāso yaṃ so ekādasannaṃ byasanānaṃ aññataraṃ byasanaṃ na nigaccheyya. "
msgstr "Any mendicant who does not abuse and insult their spiritual companions, speaking ill of the noble ones, will, without a doubt, not fall into one or other of these eleven disasters. "

#. REF: sc4
